text: Annika Roloff (born 10 March 1991) is a German athlete who specialises in the pole vault. She competed collegiately for the University of Akron, where she won the 2014 NCAA Pole Vault Championhips. She qualified for the 2016 Summer Olympics. At the 2016 Summer Olympics, she finished in 21st place in the qualifying round and did not advance to the final.
